cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision tasks, specifically multi-label classification, and proposes a method to dynamically order ground truth labels with predicted label sequences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and their optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a loss function for training the model, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of RNNs and the proposed method for multi-label classification also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, including MS-COCO and NUS-WIDE, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
